<p>
  On this page you will learn how you can deploy your app to a server
  <% if needs_install_passenger?(locals) %>
    that is running Passenger.
  <% else %>
    together with Passenger.
  <% end %>
  You can either follow these instructions with your own app, or you can use
  <% if language_type == :ruby %>
    <% git_url = "https://github.com/phusion/passenger-ruby-rails-demo.git" %>
    <a href="https://github.com/phusion/passenger-ruby-rails-demo">the sample Rails app</a> we prepared.
  <% elsif language_type == :python %>
    <% git_url = "https://github.com/phusion/passenger-python-flask-demo.git" %>
    <a href="https://github.com/phusion/passenger-python-flask-demo">the sample Flask app</a> we prepared.
  <% elsif language_type == :nodejs || language_type == :iojs %>
    <% git_url = "https://github.com/phusion/passenger-nodejs-connect-demo.git" %>
    <a href="https://github.com/phusion/passenger-nodejs-connect-demo">the sample Connect.js app</a> we prepared.
  <% elsif language_type == :meteor %>
    <% git_url = "https://github.com/phusion/passenger-meteor-leaderboard-demo.git" %>
    <a href="https://github.com/phusion/passenger-meteor-leaderboard-demo">the sample Meteor app</a> we prepared.
  <% else %>
    <% raise "No sample app known for #{language_name}" %>
  <% end %>
</p>
<p>
  If you wish to use our sample app, clone it from Github as follows:
</p>
<pre class="highlight"><span class="prompt">$ </span>git clone <%= git_url %></pre>
